!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

glass /ɡlɑːs, ˈglæs/

(glasses) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Glass is a hard, transparent substance that is used to make things such as windows and bottles. 玻璃 

例： ...a pane of glass. …一块玻璃。 

2. N-COUNT A glass is a container made from glass, which you can drink from and which does not have a handle. 玻璃杯 

例： Grossman raised the glass to his lips. 格罗斯曼把玻璃杯举到唇边。 

3. N-COUNT The contents of a glass can be referred to as a glass of something. 一玻璃杯的量 

例： ...a glass of milk. …一玻璃杯牛奶。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Glass is used to mean objects made of glass, for example drinking containers and bowls. 玻璃制品 

例： There's a glittering array of glass to choose from at markets. 市场上有大量光彩夺目的玻璃制品可供选择。 

5. N-PLURAL Glasses are two lenses in a frame that some people wear in front of their eyes in order to help them see better. 眼镜 

例： He took off his glasses. 他摘掉了眼镜。

